  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Space Complexity Interactive Explorer</title>\n<style>\n  body { font-family: monospace, monospace; color: black; background: white; margin: 1em; }\n  textarea, input[type=number], input[type=text] { font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 1em; }\n  button, input, select { margin: 0.2em 0.6em 0.4em 0; }\n  fieldset { margin-bottom: 1.2em; }\n  legend { font-weight: bold; }\n  .log, .output, .space-analysis, .workspace { white-space: pre-wrap; border: 1px solid #000; padding: 0.5em; min-height: 5em; max-height: 15em; overflow-y: auto; }\n  label { user-select: none; }\n  #structure-list button { margin: 0 0.3em 0.3em 0; }\n  #inspector > div { margin-top: 0.5em; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Space Complexity Interactive Explorer</h1>\n\n<p>\n  This tool lets you explore <strong>space complexity</strong> by \n  interactively creating algorithms, defining memory structures, running them with example inputs, and tracking detailed memory usage during execution.\n</p>\n\n<section id=\"workspace\" class=\"workspace\">\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Step 1: Define Data Structures Used</legend>\n    <p>Define named data structures with their approximate space characteristics. You can customize the definition to reflect different memory usage scenarios:</p>\n    <div>\n      <label for=\"ds-name\">Name: </label>\n      <input type=\"text\" id=\"ds-name\" placeholder=\"e.g. array\" />\n      <label for=\"ds-type\">Type: </label>\n      <select id=\"ds-type\">\n        <option value=\"primitive\">Primitive (constant size)</option>\n        <option value=\"array\">Array / List</option>\n        <option value=\"object\">Object / Dictionary</option>\n        <option value=\"recursive\">Recursive Structure</option>\n      </select>\n      <label for=\"ds-size\">Size param name (optional): </label>\n      <input type=\"text\" id=\"ds-size\" placeholder=\"e.g. n\" />\n      <label for=\"ds-desc\" title=\"Brief textual description\">Description: </label>\n      <input type=\"text\" id=\"ds-desc\" placeholder=\"e.g. dynamic array size n\" size=\"20\"/>\n      <button id=\"add-ds\">Add Structure</button>\n    </div>\n    <p>Defined structures:</p>\n    <div id=\"structure-list\"></div>\n  </fieldset>\n\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Step 2: Write the Algorithm (Pseudo-code)</legend>\n    <p>Type a pseudo-code algorithm using the defined data structures. Use a simplified language supporting variable declarations, loops, recursion, and conditional statements.</p>\n    <textarea id=\"algo-code\" rows=\"12\" cols=\"80\" spellcheck=\"false\" placeholder=\"Example:\nfunction foo(n)\n  let arr = Array of size n\n  for i = 1 to n\n    do something with arr[i]\n  end\n  return arr\nend\"></textarea>\n    <br/>\n    <button id=\"parse-algo\">Parse Algorithm</button>\n    <button id=\"clear-algo\">Clear</button>\n    <div id=\"parse-log\" class=\"log\" aria-live=\"polite\"></div>\n  </fieldset>\n\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Step 3: Provide Input Parameters</legend>\n    <p>Enter input values for the algorithm's parameters (variables used in the code header):</p>\n    <div id=\"inputs-area\"></div>\n    <button id=\"run-algo\" disabled>Run Algorithm (Simulate)</button>\n  </fieldset>\n\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Step 4: Memory Usage Simulation & Space Complexity Analysis</legend>\n    <p>\n      During simulation, track memory allocations and deallocations step by step. \n      Inspect variables, call stack, and current memory footprint.\n    </p>\n    <button id=\"step-run\" disabled>Step Forward</button>\n    <button id=\"auto-run\" disabled>Auto Run (1 step / 800ms)</button>\n    <button id=\"reset-run\" disabled>Reset</button>\n    <p>Simulation Log:</p>\n    <div id=\"sim-log\" class=\"log\" tabindex=\"0\"></div>\n    <p>Current Memory Usage:</p>\n    <div id=\"memory-usage\" class=\"space-analysis\"></div>\n    <p>Call Stack (top is current):</p>\n    <div id=\"call-stack\" class=\"space-analysis\"></div>\n  </fieldset>\n\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Step 5: Explore Space Complexity Results</legend>\n    <p>\n      Summary of space usage across steps will be shown here.\n    </p>\n    <button id=\"show-complexity\" disabled>Analyze Complexity</button>\n    <div id=\"complexity-output\" class=\"output\"></div>\n  </fieldset>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n(function(){\n  // Basic usage:\n  // User defines data structures, then types an algo in simplified pseudo-code.\n  // We parse minimal syntax, mainly to detect variables, data structures usage,\n  // simulate memory allocations (through 'let' + structures), loops, recursive calls,\n  // and track allocated sizes, deallocations.\n  //\n  // We'll maintain an abstract interpreter with memory modeled as a map of varName->spaceUsed.\n  //\n  // We offer interactive step-by-step simulation.\n  //\n  // This is NOT a full parser, but parses a highly constrained pseudo code with some syntax rules.\n  //\n  // Also track max allocated space to estimate space complexity.\n\n  // -----------------\n  // Data structures definitions:\n\n  // List of structure definitions:\n  // {id (string), name (string), type (string), sizeParam (string|null), desc (string)}\n  let structures = [];\n\n  // DOM elements\n  const dsNameInp = document.getElementById('ds-name');\n  const dsTypeSel = document.getElementById('ds-type');\n  const dsSizeInp = document.getElementById('ds-size');\n  const dsDescInp = document.getElementById('ds-desc');\n  const addDsBtn = document.getElementById('add-ds');\n  const structureListDiv = document.getElementById('structure-list');\n\n  const algoCodeText = document.getElementById('algo-code');\n  const parseAlgoBtn = document.getElementById('parse-algo');\n  const clearAlgoBtn = document.getElementById('clear-algo');\n  const parseLogDiv = document.getElementById('parse-log');\n\n  const inputsAreaDiv = document.getElementById('inputs-area');\n  const runAlgoBtn = document.getElementById('run-algo');\n\n  const stepRunBtn = document.getElementById('step-run');\n  const autoRunBtn = document.getElementById('auto-run');\n  const resetRunBtn = document.getElementById('reset-run');\n\n  const simLogDiv = document.getElementById('sim-log');\n  const memoryUsageDiv = document.getElementById('memory-usage');\n  const callStackDiv = document.getElementById('call-stack');\n\n  const showComplexityBtn = document.getElementById('show-complexity');\n  const complexityOutputDiv = document.getElementById('complexity-output');\n\n  // Generate a random ID\n  function genId() {\n    return 'id_'+Math.random().toString(36).slice(2,10);\n  }\n\n  // Add structure and update list\n  function addStructure(){\n    const name = dsNameInp.value.trim();\n    if(!name) {\n      alert(\"Structure name is required.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if(structures.some(s=>s.name === name)){\n      alert(\"Structure name must be unique.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const type = dsTypeSel.value;\n    const sizeParamRaw = dsSizeInp.value.trim();\n    const sizeParam = sizeParamRaw ? sizeParamRaw : null;\n    const desc = dsDescInp.value.trim();\n\n    const id = genId();\n    structures.push({id, name, type, sizeParam, desc});\n\n    dsNameInp.value = '';\n    dsSizeInp.value = '';\n    dsDescInp.value = '';\n\n    renderStructures();\n    parseLogDiv.textContent = '';\n  }\n\n  function renderStructures(){\n    if(structures.length === 0){\n      structureListDiv.textContent = \"(none)\";\n      return;\n    }\n    structureListDiv.textContent = '';\n    structures.forEach(s=>{\n      const btn = document.createElement('button');\n      btn.type = 'button';\n      btn.textContent = s.name+' ['+s.type+']'+(s.sizeParam? ` size param: ${s.sizeParam}`:'');\n      btn.title = s.desc || '';\n      btn.onclick = function(){\n        if(confirm(`Delete structure \"${s.name}\"?`)){\n          structures = structures.filter(x=>x.id!==s.id);\n          renderStructures();\n        }\n      };\n      structureListDiv.appendChild(btn);\n    });\n  }\n\n  addDsBtn.addEventListener('click', addStructure);\n\n  // ------------------------------------\n  // STEP 2: parse algorithm pseudo-code\n\n  // We'll do a minimal parsing:\n  //\n  // The pseudo:\n  //\n  // function <fname>([params])\n  //   statement\n  //   for ... end\n  //   if ... else ... end\n  //   let var = StructureName [of size expr]\n  //   return expr\n  // end\n  //\n  // We'll parse one function only.\n  //\n  // We'll parse statements into an AST-like structure for simulation.\n\n  // AST node types:\n  // 'function': {name, params[], body[]}\n  // 'let': {varName, structureName, sizeExpr}\n  // 'assign': {varName, expr}\n  // 'for': {varName, fromExpr, toExpr, body[]}\n  // 'if': {conditionExpr, thenBody[], elseBody[]}\n  // 'return': {expr}\n  // 'expr': evaluate expressions for this limited language (var, number)\n\n  // We'll parse expressions only as numbers, variables or 'var + number' or just variable names for index loops.\n\n  // Parsing errors appear in parseLogDiv\n\n  // We'll guard: variable names and structure names must be consistent with those defined.\n\n  // For sizes or params, variables must exist.\n\n  // Several helper functions:\n\n  // tokenize lines, remove empty lines\n\n  function parseAlgorithm(code){\n    // Reset parse log\n    parseLogDiv.textContent = '';\n\n    const linesRaw = code.split(/\\r?\\n/);\n    const lines = linesRaw.map(l=>l.trim()).filter(l=>l.length > 0 && !l.startsWith('//'));\n\n    if(lines.length === 0){\n      parseLogDiv.textContent = \"No code provided.\";\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    // First line must be function definition: function <name>([params])\n    const first = lines[0];\n    const funcMatch = first.match(/^function\\s+([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)\\s*\\(([^)]*)\\)$/);\n    if(!funcMatch){\n      parseLogDiv.textContent = \"First line must be a function definition: function name(params)\";\n      return null;\n    }\n    const funcName = funcMatch[1];\n    const paramsStr = funcMatch[2];\n    const params = paramsStr.trim() ? paramsStr.split(/\\s*,\\s*/) : [];\n\n    // Validate params names (only letters, digits or _)\n    for(let p of params){\n      if(!/^[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*$/.test(p)){\n        parseLogDiv.textContent = `Invalid parameter name: \"${p}\"`;\n        return null;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Parse the rest of the code lines until we find the matching 'end' for the function.\n    // We'll build a recursive parsing for blocks: for, if, etc.\n    // Rules: indent not required, rely on 'end' keyword lines.\n\n    // A stack of blocks. Each block: {type:'function'|'for'|'if'|'else'|'root', body:[], extra info}\n    // We start with the 'function' block for the top.\n\n    // Supported statements:\n    // let var = StructureName [of size expr]\n    // assign: var = expr\n    // for var = expr to expr\n    // if condition\n    // else\n    // return expr\n    // end\n\n    // Expression evaluation is very minimal:\n    // expr: number literals (integers),\n    // variable names,\n    // arithmetic addition: var + number or number + var (only + allowed)\n    //\n    // condition in if: var (non-zero means true), or comparison: var < number, var <= number, var == number, etc\n\n    function parseExpr(str){\n      str = str.trim();\n      // try number\n      if(/^\\d+$/.test(str)) return {type:'number', value:parseInt(str,10)};\n      // var + number or number + var\n      let m = str.match(/^([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)\\s*\\+\\s*(\\d+)$/);\n      if(m) return {type:'add', left:{type:'var', name:m[1]}, right:{type:'number', value:parseInt(m[2],10)}};\n      m = str.match(/^(\\d+)\\s*\\+\\s*([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)$/);\n      if(m) return {type:'add', left:{type:'number', value:parseInt(m[1],10)}, right:{type:'var', name:m[2]}};\n      // var only\n      if(/^[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*$/.test(str)) return {type:'var', name:str};\n      // simple comparisons for conditions:\n      m = str.match(/^([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)\\s*(<=|>=|<|>|==|!=)\\s*(\\d+)$/);\n      if(m) return {type:'cmp', left:{type:'var', name:m[1]}, op:m[2], right:{type:'number', value:parseInt(m[3],10)}};\n      // Just allow raw true or false as fallback\n      if(str === 'true') return {type:'bool', value:true};\n      if(str === 'false') return {type:'bool', value:false};\n      // More complex expr not supported\n      throw new Error(\"Cannot parse expression: \"+str);\n    }\n\n    function parseCondition(str){\n      try {\n        return parseExpr(str);\n      } catch(e){\n        throw new Error(\"Invalid condition expression: \"+e.message);\n      }\n    }\n\n    function isStatementLet(line){\n      // \"let var = StructureName [of size expr]\"\n      return /^let\\s+[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*\\s*=\\s*[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*(\\s+of\\s+size\\s+.+)?$/.test(line);\n    }\n    function parseStatementLet(line){\n      // let var = StructureName [of size expr]\n      let m = line.match(/^let\\s+([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)\\s*=\\s*([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)(?:\\s+of\\s+size\\s+(.+))?$/);\n      if(!m) throw new Error(\"Invalid let statement syntax\");\n      const varName = m[1];\n      const structName = m[2];\n      const sizeExprRaw = m[3] || null;\n      let sizeExpr = null;\n      if(sizeExprRaw !== null) {\n        sizeExpr = parseExpr(sizeExprRaw);\n      }\n      return {type:'let', varName, structName, sizeExpr};\n    }\n\n    function isStatementAssign(line){\n      // \"var = expr\" but must NOT start with let or other keywords\n      // avoid conflict with let keyword by previous test\n      return /^[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*\\s*=\\s*.+$/.test(line) && !line.startsWith('let ');\n    }\n    function parseStatementAssign(line){\n      // var= expr\n      let m = line.match(/^([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)\\s*=\\s*(.+)$/);\n      if(!m) throw new Error(\"Invalid assignment syntax\");\n      let varName = m[1];\n      let exprRaw = m[2];\n      let expr = parseExpr(exprRaw);\n      return {type:'assign', varName, expr};\n    }\n\n    function isStatementFor(line){\n      // for var = expr to expr\n      return /^for\\s+[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*\\s*=\\s*.+\\s+to\\s+.+$/.test(line);\n    }\n    function parseStatementFor(line){\n      let m = line.match(/^for\\s+([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)\\s*=\\s*(.+)\\s+to\\s+(.+)$/);\n      if(!m) throw new Error(\"Invalid for syntax\");\n      const varName = m[1];\n      const fromExpr = parseExpr(m[2]);\n      const toExpr = parseExpr(m[3]);\n      return {type:'for', varName, fromExpr, toExpr, body:[]};\n    }\n\n    function isStatementIf(line){\n      return /^if\\s+.+$/.test(line);\n    }\n    function parseStatementIf(line){\n      let m = line.match(/^if\\s+(.+)$/);\n      if(!m) throw new Error(\"Invalid if syntax\");\n      const condRaw = m[1];\n      const conditionExpr = parseCondition(condRaw);\n      return {type:'if', conditionExpr, thenBody:[], elseBody:null};\n    }\n\n    function isStatementElse(line){\n      return line === 'else';\n    }\n\n    function isStatementReturn(line){\n      return /^return\\s+.+$/.test(line);\n    }\n    function parseStatementReturn(line){\n      let m = line.match(/^return\\s+(.+)$/);\n      if(!m) throw new Error(\"Invalid return syntax\");\n      const expr = parseExpr(m[1]);\n      return {type:'return', expr};\n    }\n\n    function isStatementEnd(line){\n      return line === 'end';\n    }\n\n    // To parse function body use recursive function parseBlock(lines, startIndex)\n    // Returns {blockBody:[], nextLineIndex}\n    // blockBody is list of statements\n\n    function parseBlock(lines, fromIndex){\n      let body = [];\n      let i = fromIndex;\n      while(i < lines.length){\n        let line = lines[i];\n        // Check statement type\n        if(isStatementLet(line)){\n          try{\n            let st = parseStatementLet(line);\n            // check structName in defined structures?\n            if(!structures.some(s=>s.name === st.structName)){\n              parseLogDiv.textContent = `Line ${i+1}: Structure \"${st.structName}\" not defined`;\n              return null;\n            }\n            body.push(st);\n            i++;\n          }catch(e){\n            parseLogDiv.textContent = `Line ${i+1}: Error parsing let: `+e.message;\n            return null;\n          }\n        }\n        else if(isStatementAssign(line)){\n          try {\n            let st = parseStatementAssign(line);\n            body.push(st);\n            i++;\n          } catch(e){\n            parseLogDiv.textContent = `Line ${i+1}: Error parsing assign: `+e.message;\n            return null;\n          }\n        }\n        else if(isStatementFor(line)){\n          let forStmt;\n          try {\n            forStmt = parseStatementFor(line);\n          } catch(e){\n            parseLogDiv.textContent = `Line ${i+1}: Error parsing for: `+e.message;\n            return null;\n          }\n          i++;\n          let innerBlock = parseBlock(lines, i);\n          if(innerBlock === null) return null;\n          forStmt.body = innerBlock.blockBody;\n          i = innerBlock.nextLineIndex;\n          body.push(forStmt);\n        }\n        else if(isStatementIf(line)){\n          let ifStmt;\n          try {\n            ifStmt = parseStatementIf(line);\n          } catch(e){\n            parseLogDiv.textContent = `Line ${i+1}: Error parsing if: `+e.message;\n            return null;\n          }\n          i++;\n          let thenBlock = parseBlock(lines, i);\n          if(thenBlock === null) return null;\n          ifStmt.thenBody = thenBlock.blockBody;\n          i = thenBlock.nextLineIndex;\n          // If next line is else, parse else block\n          if(i < lines.length && isStatementElse(lines[i])){\n            i++;\n            let elseBlock = parseBlock(lines, i);\n            if(elseBlock === null) return null;\n            ifStmt.elseBody = elseBlock.blockBody;\n            i = elseBlock.nextLineIndex;\n          }\n          body.push(ifStmt);\n        }\n        else if(isStatementReturn(line)){\n          try{\n            let st = parseStatementReturn(line);\n            body.push(st);\n            i++;\n          }catch(e){\n            parseLogDiv.textContent = `Line ${i+1}: Error parsing return: `+e.message;\n            return null;\n          }\n          // Return ends the current block, so break immediately here\n          break;\n        }\n        else if(isStatementEnd(line)){\n          i++;\n          break; // end of current block\n        }\n        else {\n          parseLogDiv.textContent = `Line ${i+1}: Unknown statement or syntax: \"${line}\"`;\n          return null;\n        }\n      }\n      return {blockBody: body, nextLineIndex: i};\n    }\n\n    // Start parsing function body:\n    let bodyParsed = parseBlock(lines,1);\n    if(bodyParsed === null) return null;\n    // Check function ends properly:\n    if(bodyParsed.nextLineIndex < lines.length){\n      if(lines[bodyParsed.nextLineIndex -1] !== 'end'){\n        parseLogDiv.textContent = \"Function block missing 'end' at the end.\";\n        return null;\n      }\n    } else {\n      parseLogDiv.textContent = \"Function block missing 'end'.\";\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    let funcAST = {type:'function', name:funcName, params, body: bodyParsed.blockBody};\n\n    parseLogDiv.textContent = \"Algorithm parsed successfully.\";\n    return funcAST;\n  }\n\n  parseAlgoBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    globalContext.algoAST = parseAlgorithm(algoCodeText.value);\n    // Enable input parameters editing if parse success\n    if(globalContext.algoAST){\n      prepareInputs(globalContext.algoAST.params);\n      runAlgoBtn.disabled = false;\n      stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n      autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n      resetRunBtn.disabled = true;\n      showComplexityBtn.disabled = true;\n      simLogDiv.textContent = '';\n      memoryUsageDiv.textContent = '';\n      callStackDiv.textContent = '';\n      complexityOutputDiv.textContent = '';\n    } else {\n      inputsAreaDiv.textContent = '';\n      runAlgoBtn.disabled = true;\n    }\n  });\n\n  clearAlgoBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    algoCodeText.value = '';\n    parseLogDiv.textContent = '';\n    inputsAreaDiv.textContent = '';\n    runAlgoBtn.disabled = true;\n    stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    resetRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    showComplexityBtn.disabled = true;\n    simLogDiv.textContent = '';\n    memoryUsageDiv.textContent = '';\n    callStackDiv.textContent = '';\n    complexityOutputDiv.textContent = '';\n    globalContext = {};\n  });\n\n  // -------------------------------------\n  // STEP 3: input parameters area\n  function prepareInputs(params){\n    inputsAreaDiv.innerHTML = '';\n    if(params.length === 0){\n      inputsAreaDiv.textContent = \"This function has no parameters.\";\n      return;\n    }\n    params.forEach(p=>{\n      const lab = document.createElement('label');\n      lab.textContent = p + ': ';\n      lab.htmlFor = 'input-'+p;\n      const inp = document.createElement('input');\n      inp.type = 'number';\n      inp.min = '0';\n      inp.value = '';\n      inp.id = 'input-'+p;\n      inp.placeholder = 'Enter integer >= 0';\n      inputsAreaDiv.appendChild(lab);\n      inputsAreaDiv.appendChild(inp);\n      inputsAreaDiv.appendChild(document.createElement('br'));\n    });\n  }\n\n  // -----------------------------------\n  // STEP 4: Simulation\n\n  // We'll implement a simple abstract interpreter:\n  //\n  // State of execution:\n  // - call stack: each frame: function name, local variables, current body index, body statements, returned value\n  // - global context: structures, algorithm AST, inputs values\n  //\n  // Data structures memory cost calculation:\n  // - primitive: size=1\n  // - array/list: size param (e.g. n) determines size, so space = size param value or 1 (if missing)\n  // - object/dictionary: size param ignored, assume size 1 per instance\n  // - recursive structure: assume a fixed multiplier of input size param, default 2 if no param\n\n  // Variables allocated by let: allocate memory, unknown integer size if size param missing: take value 1 for simulation.\n\n  // Also track max memory occupied during execution and record it.\n\n  // To allow stepping, the interpreter will pause at each statement and provide a snapshot.\n\n  //\n  // We'll allow recursion: when calling function from itself,\n  // the call stack will grow and sum variables memory cumulatively.\n\n  // Implementation details:\n  // - Only one function in program.\n  // - Support only the declared parameters.\n  // - On 'let' statement, allocate memory for variable.\n  // - On assign statement, reassign variable (no additional memory effect).\n  // - On 'for' loops, repeat body from fromExpr to toExpr (both inclusive).\n  // - On 'if', evaluate condition and run thenBody or elseBody if provided.\n  // - On 'return', set function return value and pop frame.\n\n  // ---------------\n\n  let globalContext = {};\n\n  // Evaluate expression in current frame context of variables\n  function evalExpr(expr, frame, inputs){\n    switch(expr.type){\n      case 'number': return expr.value;\n      case 'var':\n        if(expr.name in frame.locals) return frame.locals[expr.name];\n        if(expr.name in inputs) return inputs[expr.name];\n        return 0; // unknown variable = 0 default\n      case 'add':\n        return evalExpr(expr.left, frame, inputs) + evalExpr(expr.right, frame, inputs);\n      case 'cmp':\n        let lval = evalExpr(expr.left, frame, inputs);\n        let rval = evalExpr(expr.right, frame, inputs);\n        switch(expr.op){\n          case '<': return lval < rval;\n          case '<=': return lval <= rval;\n          case '>': return lval > rval;\n          case '>=': return lval >= rval;\n          case '==': return lval === rval;\n          case '!=': return lval !== rval;\n          default: return false;\n        }\n      case 'bool': return expr.value;\n      default:\n        return 0;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Compute memory size for a variable of a specific structure and size param value\n  function computeMemSize(structName, sizeValue){\n    // Find structure definition\n    let def = structures.find(s=>s.name===structName);\n    if(!def) return 1; // unknown, minimal 1\n    switch(def.type){\n      case 'primitive': return 1;\n      case 'array':\n        // use sizeValue or 1 default\n        return sizeValue > 0 ? sizeValue : 1;\n      case 'object':\n        // fixed size 1 for object regardless of size param\n        return 1;\n      case 'recursive':\n        // multiply sizeValue by 2 or default 2\n        return (sizeValue > 0 ? sizeValue*2 : 2);\n      default:\n        return 1;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Simulation stack frame object:\n  // {funcAST, params, locals(varName->value), codeBody, pc: program counter, returnValue, loopStack: for-loop state}\n  // loopStack is an array for nested loops with objects:\n  // {varName, from, to, current}\n\n  // The interpreter state:\n  // callStack: Array of frames\n  // inputs: input parameters values\n  // memoryMap: varName -> memSize allocated\n  //\n  // For variable scope: local variables per frame only\n\n  // On 'let' allocate memory for varName\n  // On assign, no new memory allocated\n  // On return, free local variable memory of current frame before popping\n\n  // Keep a history of memory usage at each step\n\n  // ------------------\n\n  // Global simulation variables:\n  let callStack = [];\n  let inputsValues = {};\n  let memoryMap = {}; // varName (with frame id) -> memSize\n  let memHistory = [];\n\n  // Unique variable names across stack to track memory:\n  // We'll name variables like f0_varX for frame 0 varX, f1_varY etc.\n\n  // Helper to generate unique var id for memory map:\n  function getVarId(frameDepth, varName){\n    return `f${frameDepth}_${varName}`;\n  }\n\n  // Simulation control variables:\n  let currentStep = 0;\n  let maxAllocatedMemory = 0;\n  let autoRunnerInterval = null;\n\n  // Clear simulation states\n  function resetSimulation(){\n    callStack = [];\n    memoryMap = {};\n    memHistory = [];\n    currentStep = 0;\n    maxAllocatedMemory = 0;\n    simLogDiv.textContent = '';\n    memoryUsageDiv.textContent = '';\n    callStackDiv.textContent = '';\n    complexityOutputDiv.textContent = '';\n    stepRunBtn.disabled = false;\n    autoRunBtn.disabled = false;\n    resetRunBtn.disabled = false;\n    showComplexityBtn.disabled = false;\n  }\n\n  // Initialize simulation with the single function call with inputsValues\n  function startSimulation(funcAST, inputs){\n    callStack = [];\n    memoryMap = {};\n    memHistory = [];\n    currentStep = 0;\n    maxAllocatedMemory = 0;\n\n    inputsValues = Object.assign({}, inputs);\n\n    let frame = {\n      funcAST: funcAST,\n      params: funcAST.params,\n      locals: {},\n      codeBody: funcAST.body,\n      pc: 0,\n      returnValue: undefined,\n      loopStack: [],\n      callDepth: 0,\n      returned: false\n    };\n\n    // Set parameter values as local variables:\n    funcAST.params.forEach(p=>{\n      frame.locals[p] = inputsValues[p] !== undefined ? inputsValues[p] : 0;\n    });\n\n    callStack.push(frame);\n    updateSimLog(\"Started simulation for function: \"+funcAST.name);\n    recordMemoryUsage(\"Initial state\");\n  }\n\n  // Record current total allocated memory\n  function recordMemoryUsage(note){\n    let totalMem = Object.values(memoryMap).reduce((a,b)=>a+b,0);\n    if(totalMem > maxAllocatedMemory) maxAllocatedMemory = totalMem;\n    memHistory.push({step: currentStep, mem: totalMem, note: note});\n    displayMemoryUsage(totalMem);\n    displayCallStack();\n  }\n\n  // Display memory usage and max\n  function displayMemoryUsage(currentMem){\n    let out = `Current memory allocated: ${currentMem}\\nMax memory allocated so far: ${maxAllocatedMemory}`;\n    memoryUsageDiv.textContent = out;\n  }\n\n  // Display call stack\n  function displayCallStack(){\n    let out = '';\n    for(let i=callStack.length-1; i>=0; i--){\n      let f = callStack[i];\n      out += `#${i} Function: ${f.funcAST.name} | Locals: {`;\n      let vars = Object.entries(f.locals).map(([v,val])=>`${v}=${val}`).join(', ');\n      out += vars + '} | PC: ' + f.pc + '\\n';\n    }\n    callStackDiv.textContent = out || \"(empty)\";\n  }\n\n  // Log lines\n  function updateSimLog(str){\n    simLogDiv.textContent += `[Step ${currentStep}] ${str}\\n`;\n    simLogDiv.scrollTop = simLogDiv.scrollHeight;\n  }\n\n  // Evaluate a statement in current frame, step simulation forward\n  // Return boolean done: true if function finished, false otherwise\n  function simulateStep(){\n    if(callStack.length === 0) {\n      updateSimLog(\"Program finished.\");\n      stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n      autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n      return true;\n    }\n    currentStep++;\n\n    let frame = callStack[callStack.length - 1];\n\n    if(frame.pc >= frame.codeBody.length){\n      // End of function body reached\n      // If not returned yet, return undefined\n      if(!frame.returned){\n        frame.returnValue = undefined;\n        frame.returned = true;\n      }\n      // Free memory for locals of this frame\n      freeFrameMemory(frame);\n      callStack.pop();\n      updateSimLog(`Function ${frame.funcAST.name} ended. Return: ${frame.returnValue === undefined ? 'undefined' : frame.returnValue}`);\n      recordMemoryUsage(`Function ${frame.funcAST.name} return`);\n      return callStack.length === 0;\n    }\n\n    let stmt = frame.codeBody[frame.pc];\n\n    // Handle statement types:\n    switch(stmt.type){\n      case 'let':\n        {\n          // Evaluate allocation size\n          let sizeVal = 1;\n          if(stmt.sizeExpr){\n            try {\n              sizeVal = evalExpr(stmt.sizeExpr, frame, inputsValues);\n              if(typeof sizeVal !== 'number' || isNaN(sizeVal) || sizeVal < 0) sizeVal = 1;\n            } catch(e){ sizeVal = 1; }\n          } else {\n            // If no size param, check if structure defines sizeParam, try param variable\n            let def = structures.find(s=>s.name === stmt.structName);\n            if(def && def.sizeParam){\n              sizeVal = frame.locals[def.sizeParam] || inputsValues[def.sizeParam] || 1;\n            }\n          }\n          let memSize = computeMemSize(stmt.structName, sizeVal);\n\n          // Assign var in locals placeholder with e.g. sizeVal or zero:\n          frame.locals[stmt.varName] = sizeVal;\n\n          // Allocate memory\n          let varId = getVarId(callStack.length-1, stmt.varName);\n          memoryMap[varId] = memSize;\n\n          updateSimLog(`let ${stmt.varName} = ${stmt.structName} (size param=${sizeVal}) allocates memory ${memSize}`);\n        }\n        frame.pc++;\n        break;\n      case 'assign':\n      {\n        // Evaluate expr, assign to varName in locals\n        let val = evalExpr(stmt.expr, frame, inputsValues);\n        frame.locals[stmt.varName] = val;\n        updateSimLog(`assign ${stmt.varName} = ${val}`);\n        frame.pc++;\n        break;\n      }\n      case 'for':\n      {\n        // Handle loop iteration using loopStack\n        let loopInfo = frame.loopStack.length > 0 ? frame.loopStack[frame.loopStack.length-1] : null;\n        if(!loopInfo || loopInfo.bodyStartPc !== frame.pc){\n          // New loop at this pc\n          let fromVal = evalExpr(stmt.fromExpr, frame, inputsValues);\n          let toVal = evalExpr(stmt.toExpr, frame, inputsValues);\n          fromVal = Number(fromVal) || 0;\n          toVal = Number(toVal) || 0;\n          if(fromVal > toVal){\n            // zero iterations\n            frame.pc++;\n            updateSimLog(`for loop 0 iterations (from=${fromVal} > to=${toVal}), skip`);\n            break;\n          }\n          frame.loopStack.push({\n            varName: stmt.varName,\n            from: fromVal,\n            to: toVal,\n            current: fromVal,\n            bodyStartPc: frame.pc,\n            body: stmt.body,\n            bodyPc: 0\n          });\n          // Set loop var in locals:\n          frame.locals[stmt.varName] = fromVal;\n          updateSimLog(`Enter for loop ${stmt.varName} = ${fromVal} to ${toVal}`);\n        }\n\n        loopInfo = frame.loopStack[frame.loopStack.length - 1];\n        if(loopInfo.bodyPc >= loopInfo.body.length){\n          // Loop body ended for current iteration\n          if(loopInfo.current < loopInfo.to){\n            // next iteration:\n            loopInfo.current++;\n            frame.locals[loopInfo.varName] = loopInfo.current;\n            updateSimLog(`for loop next iteration ${loopInfo.varName} = ${loopInfo.current}`);\n            loopInfo.bodyPc = 0; // reset body pc\n          } else {\n            // Loop finished\n            updateSimLog(`for loop completed`);\n            frame.loopStack.pop();\n            frame.pc++;\n            break;\n          }\n        }\n\n        if(loopInfo.bodyPc < loopInfo.body.length){\n          // Execute statement in loop body at bodyPc\n          let stmtLoop = loopInfo.body[loopInfo.bodyPc];\n          // Simulate one statement in loop body:\n          try {\n            let res = simulateStatementInFrame(stmtLoop, frame, callStack.length-1);\n            if(res === 'pause') {\n              // pause after executing inner statement for stepping\n              loopInfo.bodyPc++;\n              return false;\n            }\n          } catch(e){\n            updateSimLog(`Error in for loop body: ${e.message}`);\n            frame.pc = frame.codeBody.length; // end function immediate\n            return false;\n          }\n          loopInfo.bodyPc++;\n          return false;\n        }\n        break;\n      }\n      case 'if':\n      {\n        let condVal = evalExpr(stmt.conditionExpr, frame, inputsValues);\n        let condBoolean = !!condVal;\n        updateSimLog(`if condition evaluated to ${condBoolean}`);\n        // We replace current codeBody/pc with thenBody or elseBody and unwind afterwards?\n        // Instead, implement like a call stack frame for blocks?\n        //\n        // Implement an internal frame stack for if blocks is complex.\n        // Alternative: inline interpret if then else as immediate block execution.\n\n        // We'll use an internal call stack inside frame for if blocks.\n        if(!frame.internalIfStack) frame.internalIfStack = [];\n        if(frame.internalIfStack.length === 0){\n          // push new if block\n          frame.internalIfStack.push({\n            type: 'if',\n            state: 'start',\n            thenBody: stmt.thenBody,\n            elseBody: stmt.elseBody,\n            pc: 0,\n            branch: condBoolean ? 'then' : 'else',\n            finished: false\n          });\n        }\n\n        let ifBlock = frame.internalIfStack[frame.internalIfStack.length-1];\n        if(ifBlock.finished){\n          // pop ifBlock and continue after if statement\n          frame.internalIfStack.pop();\n          frame.pc++;\n          return false;\n        }\n\n        let currentBody = (ifBlock.branch === 'then') ? ifBlock.thenBody : (ifBlock.elseBody || []);\n        if(ifBlock.pc >= currentBody.length){\n          ifBlock.finished = true;\n          return false;\n        }\n        // execute statement at ifBlock.pc recursively in frame, but separate from main pc\n        let stmtIf = currentBody[ifBlock.pc];\n        try {\n          let res = simulateStatementInFrame(stmtIf, frame, callStack.length-1);\n          if(res === 'pause'){\n            ifBlock.pc++;\n            return false;\n          }\n        } catch(e){\n          updateSimLog(\"Error in if block: \"+e.message);\n          frame.pc = frame.codeBody.length;\n          return false;\n        }\n        ifBlock.pc++;\n        return false;\n      }\n      case 'return':\n      {\n        let val = evalExpr(stmt.expr, frame, inputsValues);\n        frame.returnValue = val;\n        frame.returned = true;\n        updateSimLog(`return ${val}`);\n        // Free frame memory\n        freeFrameMemory(frame);\n        callStack.pop();\n        recordMemoryUsage(`Function ${frame.funcAST.name} return`);\n        // If call stack empty, program finished\n        if(callStack.length === 0){\n          updateSimLog('Program finished.');\n          stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n          autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n          return true;\n        } else {\n          // After return, update parent's pc appropriately, e.g. for recursion\n          let caller = callStack[callStack.length-1];\n          if(caller){\n            // Assign call result to something? Function calls not explicitly modeled except recursion, so no assign\n            // Pop current frame means we return to caller frame's pc+1 if this was a function call\n            caller.pc++;\n          }\n          return false;\n        }\n      }\n      default:\n        updateSimLog(\"Unsupported statement type: \"+stmt.type);\n        frame.pc++;\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    return currentStep >= 10000; // artificial step limit forced stop\n  }\n\n  // Helper to simulate one statement in a frame (used for for-body and if-body internals)\n  function simulateStatementInFrame(stmt, frame, frameDepth){\n    switch(stmt.type){\n      case 'let':\n        {\n          let sizeVal = 1;\n          if(stmt.sizeExpr){\n            try {\n              sizeVal = evalExpr(stmt.sizeExpr, frame, inputsValues);\n              if(typeof sizeVal !== 'number' || isNaN(sizeVal) || sizeVal < 0) sizeVal = 1;\n            } catch(e){ sizeVal = 1; }\n          } else {\n            let def = structures.find(s=>s.name === stmt.structName);\n            if(def && def.sizeParam){\n              sizeVal = frame.locals[def.sizeParam] || inputsValues[def.sizeParam] || 1;\n            }\n          }\n          let memSize = computeMemSize(stmt.structName, sizeVal);\n          frame.locals[stmt.varName] = sizeVal;\n          // Allocate memory with unique var id\n          // But variables in loops or inner blocks may conflict?\n          // Use combined frameDepth + current pc + varName as id for memory\n          // But that would leak allocated memory on each iteration? For simulation, assume previous declaration is overwritten (memory reused)\n          // So free previous if any:\n          let varId = getVarId(frameDepth, stmt.varName);\n          // If memory already allocated, free old first\n          if(memoryMap[varId]){\n            memoryMap[varId] = memSize; // overwrite with new size\n          } else {\n            memoryMap[varId] = memSize;\n          }\n          updateSimLog(`let ${stmt.varName} = ${stmt.structName} (size param=${sizeVal}) allocates memory ${memSize}`);\n          recordMemoryUsage(`let ${stmt.varName}`);\n\n          return 'pause';\n        }\n      case 'assign':\n        {\n          let val = evalExpr(stmt.expr, frame, inputsValues);\n          frame.locals[stmt.varName] = val;\n          updateSimLog(`assign ${stmt.varName} = ${val}`);\n          return 'pause';\n        }\n      case 'for':\n      case 'if':\n      case 'return':\n        throw new Error(\"Nested control statements not supported directly in loop or if bodies in this implementation.\");\n      default:\n        throw new Error(\"Unsupported statement type in block: \"+stmt.type);\n    }\n  }\n\n  function freeFrameMemory(frame){\n    // free all locals memory for this frame\n    let frameIdx = callStack.indexOf(frame);\n    if(frameIdx < 0) frameIdx = callStack.length; // if called after pop -1 means no frame index\n    Object.keys(frame.locals).forEach(varName=>{\n      let varId = `f${frameIdx}_${varName}`;\n      if(memoryMap[varId] !== undefined){\n        delete memoryMap[varId];\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Run simulation step event\n  stepRunBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if(!globalContext.algoAST) return;\n    let done = simulateStep();\n    if(done){\n      stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n      autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    }\n  });\n\n  autoRunBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if(autoRunnerInterval !== null){\n      // stop auto run\n      clearInterval(autoRunnerInterval);\n      autoRunnerInterval = null;\n      autoRunBtn.textContent = \"Auto Run (1 step / 800ms)\";\n      stepRunBtn.disabled = false;\n      return;\n    }\n    // start auto run\n    autoRunBtn.textContent = \"Stop Auto Run\";\n    stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    autoRunnerInterval = setInterval(function(){\n      if(callStack.length === 0){\n        clearInterval(autoRunnerInterval);\n        autoRunnerInterval = null;\n        autoRunBtn.textContent = \"Auto Run (1 step / 800ms)\";\n        stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n        autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n        return;\n      }\n      let done = simulateStep();\n      if(done){\n        clearInterval(autoRunnerInterval);\n        autoRunnerInterval = null;\n        autoRunBtn.textContent = \"Auto Run (1 step / 800ms)\";\n        stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n        autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n      }\n    }, 800);\n  });\n\n  resetRunBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if(autoRunnerInterval !== null){\n      clearInterval(autoRunnerInterval);\n      autoRunnerInterval = null;\n      autoRunBtn.textContent = \"Auto Run (1 step / 800ms)\";\n    }\n    if(globalContext.algoAST && inputsValues) {\n      startSimulation(globalContext.algoAST, inputsValues);\n      stepRunBtn.disabled = false;\n      autoRunBtn.disabled = false;\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Run full simulation from inputs when user clicks \"Run Algorithm\"\n  runAlgoBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    // collect inputs from inputs area\n    inputsValues = {};\n    let allParamsDefined = true;\n    globalContext.algoAST.params.forEach(p=>{\n      let inp = document.getElementById('input-'+p);\n      if(inp){\n        let val = parseInt(inp.value,10);\n        if(isNaN(val) || val < 0) {\n          allParamsDefined = false;\n        } else {\n          inputsValues[p] = val;\n        }\n      } else {\n        allParamsDefined = false;\n      }\n    });\n    if(!allParamsDefined){\n      alert(\"Please enter valid non-negative integer input values for all parameters\");\n      return;\n    }\n    // Start simulation from beginning:\n    startSimulation(globalContext.algoAST, inputsValues);\n    stepRunBtn.disabled = false;\n    autoRunBtn.disabled = false;\n    resetRunBtn.disabled = false;\n    showComplexityBtn.disabled = true;\n    complexityOutputDiv.textContent = '';\n    simLogDiv.textContent = '';\n  });\n\n  // ------------------------------------------\n  // Step 5: Analyze and show complexity summary\n\n  showComplexityBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if(memHistory.length === 0){\n      complexityOutputDiv.textContent = \"Run the simulation first.\";\n      return;\n    }\n    // We have memHistory: array of {step, mem}\n\n    // Approach:\n    // Show maximum memory allocated, and try to describe complexity roughly in big-O notation\n\n    // Since our simulation uses concrete input values, space complexity depends on input size.\n\n    // We'll perform simplistic heuristic:\n    // For each input parameter, try to see if max allocated memory is proportional to it or its multiples.\n\n    // We do not have symbolic analysis, so we'll only output numerical max and inputs.\n\n    let maxMem = maxAllocatedMemory;\n\n    let lines = [];\n    lines.push(`Maximum memory allocated during execution: ${maxMem}`);\n    lines.push(`Input parameters:`);\n    Object.entries(inputsValues).forEach(([k,v])=>{\n      lines.push(`  ${k} = ${v}`);\n    });\n\n    // Try to guess complexity by dividing maxMem by inputs\n    // If only one parameter, show linear or constant\n    // If multiple, show combined product estimator\n\n    let params = globalContext.algoAST.params;\n    if(params.length === 1){\n      let p = params[0];\n      let val = inputsValues[p];\n      if(val === 0) {\n        lines.push(`For ${p}=0, memory is constant.`);\n      } else {\n        let ratio = maxMem / val;\n        if(Math.abs(ratio - Math.round(ratio)) < 0.1){\n          lines.push(`Memory approx proportional to ${p} (linear O(${p}))`);\n        } else if(ratio < 1.5){\n          lines.push(`Memory roughly constant O(1) with ${p}.`);\n        } else {\n          lines.push(`Memory complexity unknown; observed memory ${maxMem} for input ${p}=${val}`);\n        }\n      }\n    } else if(params.length > 1) {\n      let product = 1;\n      params.forEach(p=>{\n        product *= inputsValues[p];\n      });\n      let ratio = maxMem / product;\n      if(Math.abs(ratio - Math.round(ratio)) < 0.1){\n        lines.push(`Memory approx proportional to product of inputs (linear O(product of inputs))`);\n      } else {\n        lines.push(`Memory complexity unknown; observed memory ${maxMem} for inputs product=${product}`);\n      }\n    } else {\n      lines.push(`No input parameters; memory constant or unknown.`);\n    }\n\n    complexityOutputDiv.textContent = lines.join('\\n');\n  });\n\n  // -----------------------------------------\n  // Initialize\n\n  renderStructures();\n\n  // Disable buttons initially\n  runAlgoBtn.disabled = true;\n  stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n  autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n  resetRunBtn.disabled = true;\n  showComplexityBtn.disabled = true;\n\n  // Add keyboard shortcut to step simulation (e.g. Space)\n  window.addEventListener('keydown', function(e){\n    if(e.code === 'Space' && !stepRunBtn.disabled){\n      e.preventDefault();\n      stepRunBtn.click();\n    }\n  });\n\n  // To improve interactivity:\n  // When user changes inputs, disable run\n  inputsAreaDiv.addEventListener('input', function(){\n    runAlgoBtn.disabled = false;\n    stepRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    autoRunBtn.disabled = true;\n    resetRunBtn.disabled = true;\n  });\n\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
